Aiming is handled in ArtillerySystem::OnLoop

For beam weapons, it randomly selects one room and then picks a second room that is
as far away from the first room as possible.

For burst weapons (eg the flak on Fed C), it picks as many targets as required.

For any other type of weapon (AFAIK this means for the flagship) it picks as many
targets as are required, but these targets are unique - it actually appears to be
possible to get the game stuck in an infinite loop if the artillery fires more
projectiles than the target ship has weapons.
